  (fun n => optimalHypothesisRateWithVaryingError ρ ε σ n)

/- The optimal hypothesis rate for a pair `(ρ, σ)` with respect to a sequence of error probabilities `ε_n` approaching 0 is bounded by the infimum of the limit superior of the logarithm of the trace of the matrix product of the measurement operator and the state, minus the logarithm of the error probability, all divided by `n`. -/
